9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 3, L.D. 39, “An Act to Require Forest
10 Landowners to Report the Registration or Sale of Their Forest Carbon Credits”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Require Landowners to Report Their Participation in a Forest Carbon
13 Program or Project'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §8881, sub-§2-A is enacted to read:
17 2-A. Forest carbon credit. "Forest carbon credit" means a unit that is equivalent to
18 one metric ton of carbon dioxide emissions or carbon dioxide equivalent emissions that are
19 avoided, removed or absorbed as a result of forest management activities that are either
20 undertaken or deferred to increase forest carbon storage or sequestration.
21 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §8881, sub-§2-B is enacted to read:
22 2-B. Forest carbon program or project. "Forest carbon program or project" means
23 a planned set of forest management activities for a defined area of forest land that is
24 designed to provide transferable forest carbon credits and that is developed to conform to
25 an existing voluntary or regulatory forest carbon protocol or registry.
26 Sec. 3. 12 MRSA §8881, sub-§2-C is enacted to read:
27 2-C. Forest carbon project developer. "Forest carbon project developer" means an
28 entity that acts on behalf of a landowner to establish forest carbon credits to meet the
29 requirements of an existing voluntary or regulatory forest carbon protocol or registry.
30 "Forest carbon project developer" also means a landowner that acts as the landowner's own
31 forest carbon project developer.
32 Sec. 4. 12 MRSA §8885, sub-§2-B is enacted to read:
33 2-B. Report on forest carbon program or project. A landowner or the landowner's
34 designated agent shall submit a report to the director whenever any portion of the
