COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 3, L.D. 39
315 landowner's forest land located in the State is enrolled in a forest carbon program or project.
326 The report must include the following information:
3 A. The name of the forest carbon program or project and the name of the forest carbon
4 project developer, if different from the landowner;
5 B. The name of the voluntary or regulatory forest carbon protocol or registry and the
6 forest carbon program or project identification number in the registry, if known;
7 C. The legal name and contact information of the landowner or landowners as of the
8 date of enrollment in the forest carbon program or project;
9 D. The period of enrollment in the forest carbon program or project of the affected
10 forest land; and
11 E. The total forest acreage enrolled in the forest carbon program or project by town,
12 township or plantation.
13 A landowner that enrolled in a forest carbon program or project prior to the effective date
14 of this subsection must file the report required pursuant to subsection 2-B by July 1, 2026.
15 Sec. 5. 12 MRSA §8885, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2003, c. 452, Pt. F, §47 and
16 affected by Pt. X, §2 and amended by PL 2011, c. 657, Pt. W, §7 and PL 2013, c. 405, Pt.
17 A, §23, is further amended to read:
18 3. Reports. Reports required under subsections 1 and, 2, 2-A and 2-B are due during
19 the month of January for the preceding year. If the period of cutting under subsection 1 or
20 2 or 2-A extends beyond December 31st of any calendar year, a report must be submitted
21 during the month of January for the preceding year. A person filing a harvest notification
22 form pursuant to section 8883‑B must complete and return to the bureau a harvest report
23 whether or not the landowner has harvested that year.'
24 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
25 number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It requires that a landowner or
2288 the landowner's designated agent report participation in a forest carbon program or project
2299 to the Director of the Bureau of Forestry within the Department of Agriculture,
3300 Conservation and Forestry. The amendment decreases the amount of information required
3311 under the bill to be included in a report of a forest carbon program or project. The
3322 amendment also eliminates the bill's requirement that an initial report for a forest carbon
3333 project over 1,000 acres in size must be accompanied by a fee of $200.
3344 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
